            "answer_text": "No. DVDs still account for nearly 60% of physical media sales, though physical media sales are in rapid decline. Having said that, I don\u2019t think they will go away anytime soon - consider that you can still buy vinyl records and even cassettes, so there is still a demand for them. Vinyl, cassettes and DVDs have been around for so long and, just as important is the fact that players are still being made for them. I think some formats, such as VHS could be considered as dead soon, because VHS players are no longer manufactured, but even so, you can still buy tapes. There are also quite a few \u2018forgotten\u2019 formats that enthusiasts are managing to keep alive, though only prolonging their inevitable demise. DVD and Blu-ray sales nearly halved over five years, MPAA report says Last known VCR maker stops production, 40 years after VHS format launch Techmoan ",
